label.value: Number of Sessions in Therapy Course
Planning Structure Generation

value.value: The method used to generate the planning structure.

label.value: Radiation Therapy Delivery Device

value.value: The type of device used to deliver the radiation therapy.

label.value: Radiotherapy Treatment Planning System

value.value: A computerized radiation therapy system that incorporates imaging of tumors into specialized plans to optimally focus beams of radiation for delivery to the intended target while avoiding critical structures that are more sensitive to radiation and thus reducing collateral damage from the therapy. Treatment planning systems are able to adjust radiotherapy targeting to compensate for the reduction in tumor size over the course of multiple treatments.

label.value: Range Shifter

value.value: A structure made of uniform material that is used to modulate the depth of the hadron beam allowing for radiation doses to be delivered to shallower volumes.

label.value: Reirradiation Value Type

value.value: The type of contribution that reirradiation generates. Component values detail the contribution from a single treatment plan. A cumulative value represents the contribution from the current plan and prior plans evaluated. The cumulative value is the basis for estimating toxicity. Recording component values as well as cumulative values enable conveying the details of the contributions form individual treatment plans.

label.value: Relative Biological Effectiveness Basis

value.value: The basis for determining the relative biological effectiveness (RBE) of an ion beam dose relative to the photon beams applied.

label.value: Repainting Technique

value.value: A method used to iteratively increment the dose from a radiation beam.

label.value: Department of Defense

value.value: Department of Defense (DOD). According to the FY2004 Defense Appropriations Act, DOD is responsible for funding of several cancer research programs such as studies on breast, ovarian, and prostate cancer, leukemia, and myeloproliferative disease.

label.value: Inter-fraction Adaptation of Treatment Plan

value.value: A treatment approach in which the plan is modified in between sessions in response to changes.

label.value: Intra-fraction Adaptation of Treatment Plan

value.value: A treatment approach in which the plan is modified during the treatment session in response to changes.

label.value: Revision of Treatment Plan

value.value: A treatment approach in which the plan is modified, but not due to changes arising from intent to adapt, such as when the patient's position changes and the patient is re-scanned.

label.value: Age at Image Acquisition

label.value: Advisory Committee to the Director, NCI

value.value: The Committee advises and makes recommendations to the Director, NCI, for the oversight and integration of various planning and advisory groups serving the broad programmatic and institutional objectives of the Institute. The Committee serves as the official channel through which the findings and recommendations emerging from these groups are submitted to the NCI. The Committee may consider the reports of the various review groups as informational, advisory, or as recommendations, and shall provide the NCI with assistance in identifying opportunities to be pursued within the areas of cancer research that cut across the intramural and extramural programs.

label.value: NCI Director's Consumer Liaison Group

value.value: The Director's Consumer Liaison Group (DCLG) is a group of fifteen members of the cancer advocacy community who were convened to help NCI increase the representation of the cancer advocacy community on NCI advisory committees, and increase their involvement in program and policy development.  DCLG members will interact directly with the scientific community at NCI on a wide range of programs and issues. The DCLG will also help NCI to widen the pool of qualified consumer-advocates who can be called upon to serve on NCI advisory committees and other groups. (2/99)

label.value: Date of Report at Diagnosis and Staging of Prostate Cancer

value.value: The date on which the diagnosis and staging of prostate cancer was reported.

label.value: Multiple Static Segments Radiation Therapy Delivery Method

value.value: Delivery of radiation therapy executed sequentially following movement of the multileaf collimator (MLC) leaves. MLC leaves cannot be moved when the beam is activated so leaf motion and radiation delivery occur independently.

label.value: Sliding Window Radiation Therapy Delivery Method

value.value: Delivery of radiation therapy by moving the multileaf collimator (MLC) leaves from one field side to another.

label.value: Optical Instrument

value.value: An instrument used to measure an event involving emission, absorption, or refraction of light.

label.value: Multi-field Optimization

value.value: An optimization method where the spot positions and weights of all the proton field are optimized together.

label.value: Optimization to CTV

value.value: Optimization of the radiation treatment plan based on the clinical target volume (CTV).

label.value: Optimization to PTV

value.value: Optimization of the radiation treatment plan based on the planning target volume (PTV).

label.value: Single Field Optimization

value.value: An optimization method where the spot positions and weights of each proton field are optimized individually.

label.value: Androgen Deprivation Agent Dosage Unit

value.value: The unit of measure that is associated with the dose of an administered androgen deprivation agent.

label.value: Antineoplastic Agent Dosage Unit

value.value: The unit of measure that is associated with the dose of an administered antineoplastic agent.

label.value: Immunotherapeutic Agent Dosage Unit

label.value: Reirradiation Evaluation Course Names

value.value: The names of the courses contributing to the reported dose-volume histogram (DVH) metric value for the structure.
